		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Planetside 2
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1767359">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							A few of my friends and I are playing it (most of us were quite big into the original as well) and it's been a blast. Balance-wise seems to be pretty good (infantry aren't completely powerless against vehicles, etc). Free-to-play is huge and there really isn't any &quot;pay-to-win&quot;. Most of the stuff you pay for is cosmetic (different graphics for armor pieces, accessories for vehicles, etc). You can pay to unlock guns as well, but all gun unlocks can be unlocked via cert points as well and the default guns for the most part are just as capable as the unlockables (they tout unlockables as being &quot;sidegrades&quot; which again, for the most part, is true).<br />
<br />
The real meat where differences in guns comes from is in the gun modifications, none of which is unlockable through money (only via cert points). Things like different scopes, suppressors, etc. You can also get armor modifications which are also only unlockable through cert points (ability to use C4, augments to your class abilities, etc).<br />
<br />
I have found that it is infinitely more fun to play with people you know as a solo player won't tend to get very far, but ymmv. Above all else, though, it's F2P so why not give it a whirl?
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
